<img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2027392 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-897x598.jpeg" alt="" width="897" height="598" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-897x598.jpeg 897w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-1728x1152.jpeg 1728w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-320x213.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-640x427.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/La-Pelosa-Beach-Sardinia-Italy-600x400.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 897px) 100vw, 897px" /> One of the most beautiful and fantastic destinations to visit is a beach. The tranquillity and comfort at the beach are unmatched. It is hard to list the top beaches in the world because tourists have diverse tastes ranging from security, relaxation, scenery, accessibility, aesthetics, and more. Whether they’re blessed with attractive, bright white fine sand or located in the best setting imaginable, the beach will always be a top option. This article highlights some of the most gorgeous beaches to visit in the world. Nungwi Beach, Tanzania: Nungwi is a popular beach location on the Tanzanian island of Zanzibar, located at the island’s northwestern tip. The beach is one of the prettiest and most popular beaches in Zanzibar. Nungwi Beach has beautiful features such as lovely clean waves from something like the Indian Ocean and smooth white sand. It is also known for its crystal blue waters and exotic flora and fauna. It has amazing sunset views, and all restaurants and clubs on the beach are open until late hours. On the powdery sand, you can take in the ocean scenery while participating in other beach activities. Whitehaven Beach, Queensland, Australia: The largest beach in the Whitsundays is Whitehaven; this gorgeous beach is incomparable in Australia. This beach has beautiful white sand that is 98 percent pure silica. It makes the sand incredibly smooth and delicate. Even on days when the weather is very hot, walking barefoot is comfortable because it doesn’t absorb heat like other types of sand beaches do. Whitehaven Beach is also known for its charming Hill Inlet. Travelers really do need to take the opportunity to visit this beach.
