Pink Sand Beach, Harbour Island, The Bahamas: On Harbour Island in the Bahamas is the pink sand beach. Because of its pink sands, this beach is very attractive and unique. A microscopic organism with a reddish-pink shell known as a foraminifera is the source of the pink sand beach’s color on Harbour Island in the Bahamas. Swimming in this beach is slightly safer because the turquoise water in this area is usually calm and shallow due to the protection provided by the surrounding beaches. It is also great to sight see. La Pelosa Beach, Sardinia, Italy: La Pelosa is a small beach, just about 300 meters long and no more than 60 meters wide. La Pelosa Beach is one of the most beautiful and well visited beaches in Sardinia. It has been a popular destination for tourists due to its fine sand, shallow, clear water, very gorgeous setting, and structure. On a scorching summer day, it’s the ideal spot for relaxing as it is quite exposed to the wind. Camps Bay Beach: Camps Bay Beach is located in Cape Town, South Africa. It is a very beautiful and attractive beach for tourists to visit. Camps Bay Beach is a very safe and clean environment that is conducive enough for friends and family. It is the ideal location for exciting group activities, romantic activities, and so on. It is also known for its lovely white sand and fantastic views of the water and the mountains of Lion’s Head and the Twelve Apostles. 